<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="pvm_gsize">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>pvm_gsize</refname>
    <refpurpose>  returns the number of members presently in the named group.  </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[nb] = pvm_gsize(group)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>group</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>string, string group name of an existing group.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>nb</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>integer, returning the number of members presently in the group.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>pvm_gsize</literal> returns the size of
    the group named <literal>group</literal></para>
    <para>
    The returned value <literal>nb</literal>will be &gt;= 0 if 
    the call is successful and will be 
    will be &lt; 0 if some error occurs.</para>
    <para>
    Since groups can change dynamically in PVM 3.0,
    this routine can only guarantee to return the instantaneous
    size of a given group.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection role="see also">
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member>
        <link linkend="pvm_joingroup">pvm_joingroup</link>
      </member>
    </simplelist>
  </refsection>
</refentry>
